# Terminology

Use the following terms consistently.
Do not use listed variants unless they appear in code, URLs, or direct quotations.

| Required term                         | Do not use                                              |
|---------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Web3Signer                            | web3signer, Web3signer, WEB3SIGNER (except in code/URLs/CLI) |
| Consensys Web3Signer                  | ConsenSys Web3Signer                                     |
| remote signing service                | remote signer service (unless quoting)                  |
| signing service                       | signer service                                           |
| key management                        | keys management                                          |
| keystore                              | key store, key-store                                     |
| slashing protection                   | slash protection                                         |
| validator client                      | validator node (unless explicitly discussing nodes)     |
| execution layer                       | Ethereum 1.0 (note former name on first use only)       |
| consensus layer                       | Ethereum 2.0 (note former name on first use only)       |
| fee recipient                         | feeRecipient                                             |
| JSON-RPC                              | json-rpc, Json-RPC, JSONRPC                              |
| REST API                              | rest api, REST endpoints API                            |

## Key types and vaults

- Write signing key types as `secp256k1` and `BLS12-381`.
- Capitalize vault product names as their vendors do: HashiCorp, Azure Key Vault,
  AWS Secrets Manager, AWS KMS, Google Cloud Secret Manager.

## Standards and specifications

On first mention in a page, spell out standards with identifier in parentheses.
Use the short form after first use.

Examples:

- First use: "Ethereum Improvement Proposal 3076 (EIP-3076)"
- Subsequent: "EIP-3076"
- First use: "Engine API specification"
- Subsequent: "Engine API"
